Why Github?

Github is a good way to keep backup of our works. It is referred as a version control system that allows to store the development process in secure. Also it is a good way to collaborate with other developers as it makes it easy to download older version and upload with newer version. Personally, I find it very useful to illustrate my works to people who are interested in what I do. [vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]

   About Project Gollaba

  Gollaba, meaning 'to choose' in Korean, is a web platform for Emory community, reinforcing the trade experience between students. The idea originated from Emory Buy & Sell community within Facebook. The Emory Facebook forum holds limits when trading goods. To enhance trading experience, we made a independent web application that functions similar to the forum with better interface such as categorization and transaction. Also, we have managed to improve product browsing and contacting with ease.      

Team DECK

 

DECK is our Scrum team name consist of 4 members. Our team followed the Scrum Methodology, and applied Scrum concepts, therefore, we successfully deployed our web platform. We constructed milestones of 9 sprints in detail to meet the deploy deadline. Our team conducted a meeting every week to summarize individual work and to support each other to increase the speed and the accuracy of work progress.

DANIEL

[/wr_vc_section_text][wr_vc_section_text color="#a3a3a3" font_size="13px" text_align="center"]Software & Web developer[/wr_vc_section_text][wr_vc_section_text color="#3c3eb2" font_size="15px" text_align="center"] Contact Me[/wr_vc_section_text][vc_column_text]

Resume

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][wr_vc_section_text color="#000000" font_size="20px" text_transform="uppercase"]

General Information

[/wr_vc_section_text][wr_vc_section_text color="#3f3f3f"]I am software and web developer. I also like to design and listen to music on daily basis. I have a bachelor science degree in Computer Science and Mathematics from Emory University. I have experience in living at three different countries with different speaking language. Settling to new environment? Easy as pie. I am highly motivated and enthusiastic in learning new things. I am also willing to learn, work and communicate well with others without letting anyone down including myself. Challenges has always been around me and I have enjoyed them with positive spirit and attitude using it as an opportunity to develop not only software but me. I am always up for new exciting challenges and to expand my knowledge. I am ready to give my best effort to bring the best result out of my work.
Give up is not in my dictionary. Thank you Napoleon -Dongsun Yoon
[/wr_vc_section_text][wr_vc_bar height="30px"][wr_vc_section_text font_size="20px" text_transform="uppercase"]

Timeline

[/wr_vc_section_text][wr_vc_bar height="30px"][wr_vc_section_text font_size="20px" text_transform="uppercase"][/wr_vc_section_text] [timeline-express]

My Offer

[wr_vc_section_text color="#3f3f3f"]Software nowadays is developing with extreme fast pace. I know that I still have a long way to dig further to obtain computer programming skills. I am also well aware of myself that I lack in participation to various projects. However, I can guarantee that I will learn fast, show my enthusiasm, share ideas and work well alone or together. I been in the position that requires leadership multiple times. I was president when I was in 6th grade, student council during  sophomore at high school, soccer captain of my Lagrange Academic team, and drill sergeant during my military duty. I have trained about 2200 soldiers, meaning I have met around 2200 different people with different characteristics. My duty was to lead and train people to get along during their training period. I know well how team work operates and how to encourage people to work together as a team. I am ready to become a good member for your team. People around me say I have strong positive character traits and I can assure you with the fact that I am mentally strong person, hard worker and joyful to work with. item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][wr_vc_section_image img_url="867" width="100px" height="100px"][wr_vc_section_text color="#afafaf"]This logo idea came from an icon representing code : </> </ is for D and <> is for S making DS my initial. [/wr_vc_section_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][wr_vc_section_text font_size="20px"]How to express myself to You without boredom? How to organize and express my ideas into private space? I came up with yoonds.com, my own private platform to show what I am capable of. I fully used this opportunity to understand and obtain knowledge of developing and designing website.[/wr_vc_section_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][wr_vc_section_image img_url="896" width="100px" height="100px"][wr_vc_section_text color="#afafaf"]This favicon given by my brother, the green letter ㄷ is my name's initial in Korean character and the color green represents the color of the year 2017.[/wr_vc_section_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][wr_vc_section_text]

Motivation

[/wr_vc_section_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="3/4"][wr_vc_section_text] As a programmer I wanted to challenge myself to not only represent my accomplishment but also to express my ideas and show creativeness. I have not had enough opportunity to present my ideas to real world application, therefore, with yoonds, I have managed to learn what it is like to apply my imagination and ideas to website. Today's world have dynamic social networking platforms. I convinced myself, why not have independent one for myself including anything that I want to express? Here, yoonds.com has been launched.[/wr_vc_section_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][wr_vc_bar height="30px"][wr_vc_section_text]

Accomplishment

[/wr_vc_section_text][wr_vc_section_text]From brainstorming ideas on how to express myself into website to web designing of visual and content with software implementation, are constructed and produced by DongSun Yoon. The entire process of building my own website has not only been academically useful in a way of learning PHP, HTML, CSS and Wordpress but also has been joyful and fun, reminding excitement when developing a website. I hope you have enjoyed visiting my website as much as I enjoyed myself. Yoonds is an ongoing website that I will update whenever new content and idea is avaliable.[/wr_vc_section_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][wr_vc_bar height="35px"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/3"][wr_vc_section_text color="#dd0f0f"]

Ulsan, South Korea (9 years) -> Istanbul, Turkey (5 years) -> Seoul, South Korea (3 years) -> Lagrange GA, US (3 years) -> Nonsan, South Korea (2 years) -> Atlanta GA, US (3 years)

I have no fear in facing new environment. I am ready and will assimilate without problem.

item.title: Fast Learner
item.dc:creator: yoonds7
item.content:encoded:
I began studying in the field of Computer Science during my third year of College. I have changed my study interest from Pre-Med to Computer Science when I got back from Military duty that was held in South Korea. The very first language I learned was JAVA and I quickly fell in love as I started learning more languages such as C, MYSQL, Assembly and MATLAB.

I studied php and html (phtml) independently as I began to develop web pages. There are still more to learn and I am ready to learn new Computer languages such as R, Python and so on.
